data.name: label1.Text
data.value: This section is for beginners. It shows you the most basic tools to get things done.

data.name: lblAIOInt.Text
data.value:
Use this tool to integrate your updates, drivers, theme packs, tweaks, language packs, anything really. You do not need to mount the image first with WIM Manager as it will be automatically mounted for you.
This is the ultimate tool to keep your images completely up-to-date and save you many man hours!

data.name: label5.Text
data.value: The ISO Maker allows you to make new *.iso images to either mount or burn your customized image. It contains options to rebuild your image to help reduce its size and even supports creating UEFI bootable DVDs!

data.name: label3.Text
data.value: If you don't like installing from DVD, use this tool to make your USB drive bootable. You can prepare even your USB stick without losing any data!

data.name: label2.Text
data.value: This section is for users with a bit more experience with this tool and modifying images.

data.name: label13.Text
data.value: This is for when you want to create ISOs with both x64 and x86 images. You can also use it to make a Windows 7 and Vista AIO disk if you really wanted to.

data.name: label14.Text
data.value: Make unattended installs; self-explanatory really. You can use WIM Manager to integrate your newly created unattended file into your DVD.

data.name: label16.Text
data.value: This tools lets you mount, unmount, delete, rename, import, export images, etc.. Think of it as a GDISM/GImagex tool.

data.name: label4.Text
data.value: This section is for the most experienced users. USE WITH CAUTION!

data.name: label17.Text
data.value:
Remove built-in packages like 'Windows Media Player' to make your offline installation smaller. Please make sure you test your saved image with a virtual machine first.
NOTE: This tool mostly uses Microsoft's method of removing packages. It will mainly affect OS size after installation.

data.name: label18.Text
data.value:
This is basically 'regedit.exe', but with the registry displayed within the mounted image. You can also import registry files to so your custom made tweaks will be in your mounted image after installation.
CAUTION: Only use this if you have experience with Windows registry editor. This can seriously cause damage!

data.name: label30.Text
data.value: Keep your Windows images up-to-date. Useful for those who install on many machines.

data.name: label8.Text
data.value:
An external tool to keep your collection of Windows 7, Windows 8.1, Windows 10, Office 2013 and Office 2016 updates up-to-date.
Credits: Alphawaves @MDL

data.name: cmdBrowseUpdateCache.ToolTipText
data.value: Opens the updateCache.db file in your default browser.

data.name: cmdForum.ToolTipText
data.value: Visit the homepage of Win Toolkit!

data.name: cmdAbout.ToolTipText
data.value: View what has changed since the last release.

data.name: cmdGuides.ToolTipText
data.value:
Learn how to use Win Toolkit. Guides are available with step-by-step information about all the features implemented.
NOTE: Do not post bugs in the 'Guides' part of the forum.

data.name: cmdWindowsISO.ToolTipText
data.value: Download the Windows ISOs free and legally!

data.name: cmdDWin7SP1LangPacks.ToolTipText
data.value: Download Language Packs so your Windows 7 SP1 image is available in any language you want!

data.name: cmdDAddons.ToolTipText
data.value: Download addons which you can integrate into your Windows 7 image.

data.name: cmdDSFX.ToolTipText
data.value: Download pre-made SFX files. These are programs which have been made to install silently. They work perfectly with Silent Installer via the All-In-One Integrator.

data.name: cmdDThemePacks.ToolTipText
data.value: Download themes which you can integrate, so after Windows 7 is installed you have more themes.

data.name: cmdDWallpapers.ToolTipText
data.value: Download Wallpapers, which you can integrate into your Windows 7 image.

data.name: cmdDVirtualPC.ToolTipText
data.value: Windows Virtual PC is the Microsoft virtualization technology. You can use it to run more than one operating system at the same time on one computer, and to run many productivity applications on a virtual Windows environment, with a single click, directly from a computer running Windows 7.

data.name: cmdDVirtualBox.ToolTipText
data.value: VirtualBox is a virtualization product for enterprise as well as home use. VirtualBox is an extremely featured rich, high performance product for enterprise customers which runs on Windows, Linux, Macintosh, and Solaris hosts and supports a large number of guest operating systems including but not limited to Windows (NT 4.0, 2000, XP, Server 2003, Vista, Windows 7), DOS/Windows 3.x, Linux (2.4 and 2.6), Solaris and OpenSolaris, OS/2, and OpenBSD.

data.name: cmdDXPMode.ToolTipText
data.value: Windows 7 has several built-in tools to help with program compatibility and Windows XP programs should be installed directly on Windows 7. Windows XP Mode runs many older Windows XP productivity programs and that are not natively compatible with Windows 7, thus helping realize cost savings and reduce possible operational downtime by extending the life of existing software. Visit the Windows 7 Compatibility Center to find software that works with Windows 7.

data.name: cmdVMWare.ToolTipText
data.value: VMware Player Plus is the best way to deliver a managed desktop to all of your employees, students, contractors, partners or customers

data.name: cmdDGoogleChrome.ToolTipText
data.value: Google Chrome runs websites and applications with lightning speed. A browser that combines a minimal design with new technology designed to improve the user experience.

data.name: cmdDFirefox.ToolTipText
data.value: Download the new Firefox Browser for a faster, safer and better web experience.

data.name: cmdDOpera.ToolTipText
data.value: Opera is a web browser and Internet suite developed by Opera Software with over 270 million users worldwide. It offers free and easy to download Web browsers for computers, mobile phones and devices.

data.name: cmdDSafari.ToolTipText
data.value: Safari puts the emphasis on browsing, not the browser. Innovative features make your experience on the web better than it ever was.

data.name: cmdDDISM.ToolTipText
data.value: Download DISM so you can use this tool on Windows XP or Windows Vista.

data.name: cmdDSlim451Installer.ToolTipText
data.value: This package contains the full version of the x86/x64 .NET Framework 4.5 installer, including updates (thanks to Komm, McRip, PointZero) already integrated. The reason it's called 'Slim' is because the original MSI installers were edited to remove unnecessary setup junk (special thanks to yumeyao & dumpydooby). This should save you 200+ MB of space on your HDD.

data.name: mnuDownloads.ToolTipText
data.value: Download files which can be used to improve your new images!

data.name: cmdLangToCab.ToolTipText
data.value: Convert language packs *.exe into *.cab files for integration.

data.name: cmdExeToMsp.ToolTipText
data.value: Office updates are downloaded in *.exe format. To include them with an Office installation, they need to be *.msp format.

data.name: cmdMsuToCab.ToolTipText
data.value: Convert Microsoft update files *.msu into *.cab files.

data.name: cmdCaptureImage.ToolTipText
data.value: Capture a folder into a new or existing *.wim file.

data.name: cmdSWMMerger.ToolTipText
data.value: Convert multiple *.swm files into a single editable *.wim file.

data.name: cmdWIMSplitter.ToolTipText
data.value: Convert editable *.wim file into multiple read-only *.swm files for smaller CDs.

data.name: cmdDriverInstaller.ToolTipText
data.value: Install drivers into your currently installed system.

data.name: cmdUpdateInstaller.ToolTipText
data.value: Install updates into your currently installed system. Useful for update repository users.

data.name: cmdAddonMaker.ToolTipText
data.value: Create addons (*.WA files) which are used to have programs pre-installed with your image.

data.name: cmdUpdateRetriever.ToolTipText
data.value: Detect *.cab files and scan WindowsUpdate.log for new updates received via Windows Update.

data.name: toolStripMenuItem1.ToolTipText
data.value: Extra tools to help your integration process.

data.name: cmdOptions.ToolTipText
data.value: Change important settings for Win Toolkit.

data.name: cmdReportBug.ToolTipText
data.value: Report a bug on the Win Toolkit forum. Please remember to attach any error logs within the WinToolkit.exe folder.
